Definition: In this task you are given an array of integers, check if it is monotonic or not. If yes, then return 1, else return 2. An array is monotonic if it is either monotone increasing or monotone decreasing. An array nums is monotone increasing if for all i <= j, nums[i] <= nums[j]. An array nums is monotone decreasing if for all i <= j, nums[i] >= nums[j]

Negative Examples.explanation: The array is not monotonic as 1 < 3 > 2
